Visualização de Dados com Python

Visualização de Dados com Python

MatPlotLib

%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# Equivalente ao seq() no R
x = np.linspace(0,10,100)

#Garfico de x em relação ao seu seno
## r de Red e -- para ser pontilhado
plt.plot(x, np.sin(x), 'r--')
plt.show()

Seaborn: statistical data visualization

%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

plt.plot(x, np.sin(x), 'b--')
plt.plot(x, np.cos(x), 'r--')
plt.show()


import seaborn as sns
##Caso de o erro: ImportError: No module named 'scipy._lib.decorator'
###Use: sudo apt-get install python-scipy ; sudo pip3 install -U scipy

#Rodando o mesmo comando
sns.set_style('darkgrid')
plt.plot(x, np.sin(x), 'b--')
plt.plot(x, np.cos(x), 'r--')
plt.show()

Histograma e gráfico de setores

%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import pydataset

pydataset.data('titanic', show_doc= True)

titanic

PyDataset Documentation (adopted from R Documentation. The displayed examples are in R)

## titanic

### Description

The data is an observation-based version of the 1912 Titanic passenger
survival log,

### Usage

    data(titanic)

### Format

A data frame with 1316 observations on the following 4 variables.

`class`

a factor with levels `1st class` `2nd class` `3rd class` `crew`

`age`

a factor with levels `child` `adults`

`sex`

a factor with levels `women` `man`

`survived`

a factor with levels `no` `yes`

### Details

titanic is saved as a data frame. Used to assess risk ratios

### Source

Found in many other texts

### References

Hilbe, Joseph M (2014), Modeling Count Data, Cambridge University Press Hilbe,
Joseph M (2007, 2011), Negative Binomial Regression, Cambridge University
Press Hilbe, Joseph M (2009), Logistic Regression Models, Chapman & Hall/CRC

### Examples

    data(titanic)
    titanic$survival <- titanic$survived == "yes"
    glmlr <- glm(survival ~ age + sex + factor(class), family=binomial, data=titanic)
    summary(glmlr)

#Importando o data set
titanic = pydataset.data('titanic')

pydataset.data('LakeHuron')['LakeHuron'].hist()
plt.show()


pydataset.data('LakeHuron')['LakeHuron'].hist(orientation = 'horizontal')
plt.show()


dados = pydataset.data('LakeHuron').head()
dados['percent'] = dados['LakeHuron']/dados['LakeHuron'].sum()
plt.pie(dados['percent'], labels = dados['time'])
plt.show()


plt.pie(dados['percent'], labels = dados['time'], autopct='%1.2f%%')
plt.show()

Gráfico de Dispersão

%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import pydataset

pydataset.data('AirPassengers').head()
time AirPassengers
1 1949.000000 112
2 1949.083333 118
3 1949.166667 132
4 1949.250000 129
5 1949.333333 121 
df = pydataset.data('AirPassengers')
plt.plot(df['time'], df['AirPassengers'])
plt.show()


plt.scatter(df['time'], df['AirPassengers'])
plt.show()


iris = pydataset.data('iris')
iris.head()
Sepal.Length Sepal.Width Petal.Length Petal.Width Species
1 5.1 3.5 1.4 0.2 setosa
2 4.9 3.0 1.4 0.2 setosa
3 4.7 3.2 1.3 0.2 setosa
4 4.6 3.1 1.5 0.2 setosa
5 5.0 3.6 1.4 0.2 setosa 
plt.scatter(iris['Sepal.Length'], iris['Sepal.Width'], sizes = 10 * iris['Petal.Length'])
plt.show()


#Criando a função para mudar a cor para cada espécie

def specie_color(x):
    if(x == 'setosa'):
        return 0
    elif(x == 'versicolor'):
        return 1
    return 2
#Crando uma nova coluna

iris['Specie_Number'] = iris['Species'].apply(specie_color)
iris.head()
Sepal.Length Sepal.Width Petal.Length Petal.Width Species Specie_Number
1 5.1 3.5 1.4 0.2 setosa 0
2 4.9 3.0 1.4 0.2 setosa 0
3 4.7 3.2 1.3 0.2 setosa 0
4 4.6 3.1 1.5 0.2 setosa 0
5 5.0 3.6 1.4 0.2 setosa 0 
plt.scatter(iris['Sepal.Length'], iris['Sepal.Width'], sizes = 10 * iris['Petal.Length'], 
            c = iris['Specie_Number'], cmap = 'viridis', alpha= 0.6)
plt.show()

Customizando Eixos e Labels de um Gráfico

%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

#https://www.kaggle.com/mguzmann/swedishcrime
df = pd.read_csv('reported.csv')
df.head()

#Trocando NaN por 0
df.fillna(0, inplace= True)

plt.plot(df['Year'], df['crimes.total'], '-r')
plt.plot(df['Year'], df['crimes.person'], '--b')
plt.show()


fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(df['Year'], df['crimes.total'], '-r')
ax.plot(df['Year'], df['crimes.person'], '--b')
ax.legend(loc = 'upper left')
plt.show()


fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(df['Year'], df['crimes.total'], '-r')
ax.plot(df['Year'], df['crimes.person'], '--b')
ax.legend(loc = 'upper left')
ax.set_ylabel('Quantidade')
ax.set_xlabel('Ano')
ax.set_title('Crimes: Total x Person')
ax.set_xlim([df['Year'].min(), df['Year'].max()])
plt.show()

Criando Mapas

%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

#Importando um csv
df = pd.read_csv('copacabana_lat_lng.csv')
df.head()

plt.scatter(df['lng'], df['lat'], marker='.')
plt.show()


import mplleaflet
plt.scatter(df['lng'], df['lat'], marker='.')
mplleaflet.display()
